    "In addition to the linguistic messages to be expressed, the acoustic messages can also deliver rich information (such as age, gender, and hometown).",
    "Acoustic expressions are described by speech prosody (pitch, loudness, rhythm).",
    "A happy voice usually has a higher pitch, and a louder and faster speech rate, whereas a sad voice has a lower pitch and slower speech rate.There are two opinions on acoustic expressions [43].",
